hopobject.body: I'll text you later hydroxyzine pamoate 25 mg tablet The term has been used worldwide by everyone from Bill Clinton to Katie Price ever since the suffragettes achieved their goal and won women the right to have a political say. But, some 95 years later, what does the women’s vote actually mean? Do I, as a woman who votes, go to the ballot box with a set of criteria in my mind that vary from my male friends’? Do women generally vote differently to men, and if so, why don’t politicians ever discuss the ‘men’s vote’?
